<TITLE> More ornaments recovered in BRAC Bank heist </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Police Friday recovered another 51 bhori in gold and diamond ornaments from a suspect allegedly tied to the BRAC Bank lockers heist. Following the confession of Maheb Alam Chowdhury, who was arrested from Gulistan in the capital Thursday, Detective Branch of police recovered the ornaments in a raid on his Mirpur home. Additional deputy police commissioner of Dhaka Metropolitan Police Detective Branch Asaduzzaman said police arrested the main suspect in the robbery Raja Miah, and two others, Thursday from Sreenagar in Munshiganj. During interrogation Raja Miah disclosed the name of Maheb as his accomplice in the robbery of the lockers at the BRAC Bank's Dhanmondi branch in Sukrabad. Police raided Maheb's house and recovered the gold and diamond ornaments by digging the floor of the house. They also recovered three cheque books of Sonali Bank's Mirpur branch along with the ornaments. Asaduzzaman said a special key was used to open the lockers. Police are examining whether the hotel and bank employees were involved in the robbery. bdnews24.c
